WEBVTT

00:00.001 --> 00:01.024
<i>Previously on</i> The Originals...

00:01.026 --> 00:03.047
<i>She's gathering up all of
you to take back the power</i>

00:03.049 --> 00:04.503
that's been split up inside of you.

00:04.506 --> 00:07.359
Ever since I took the
power back, the whispers...

00:07.362 --> 00:10.890
<i>I can't think, I can't
sleep, I can't even breathe.</i>

00:10.893 --> 00:12.582
You'll forget meeting me here today.

00:12.585 --> 00:14.830
Hayley Marshall is now at peace.

00:14.833 --> 00:15.965
And with that,

00:15.968 --> 00:17.554
you'll be at peace yourself.

00:17.557 --> 00:18.966
Should we expect your brother?

00:18.968 --> 00:20.575
Roman knows that he's not welcome

00:20.578 --> 00:22.442
in this city, after the part he played

00:22.445 --> 00:23.670
in my mother's plan.

00:23.672 --> 00:26.673
Are the werewolves
really worth dying for?

00:26.675 --> 00:28.041
You're damn right.

00:32.214 --> 00:33.947
So, what, did he just
come here to bluff?

00:33.949 --> 00:35.802
He wanted to find out what
side I was gonna choose.

00:35.804 --> 00:37.476
<i>And he wanted to punish me.</i>

00:37.479 --> 00:39.607
- To peace.
- ALL: To peace.

00:40.589 --> 00:42.089
[COUGHS]

00:42.091 --> 00:44.324
- [ALL COUGHING, GAGGING]
- VINCENT: Ivy!

00:46.629 --> 00:48.234
Is this the rest of my life?

00:48.237 --> 00:51.330
<i>A rage that can only
be quieted by violence?</i>

00:51.333 --> 00:53.934
Hope, if violence is what
you need to feel better,

00:53.936 --> 00:56.537
then you have the perfect father.

00:57.907 --> 01:00.073
[INDISTINCT WHISPERING]

01:01.210 --> 01:03.343
[GRUNTS]

01:06.015 --> 01:07.614
Do it again.

01:07.616 --> 01:09.650
Harder this time.

01:09.652 --> 01:10.918
[WHISPERING CONTINUES]

01:10.920 --> 01:13.166
All of that pain, that
simmering darkness.

01:13.169 --> 01:15.123
You need to purge it
before it eats you alive.

01:15.126 --> 01:17.448
- Dad...
- Give me your anger, Hope!

01:17.451 --> 01:19.184
[SCREAMS]

01:24.166 --> 01:26.033
[BOTH PANTING]

01:27.169 --> 01:29.336
It's not working.

01:29.338 --> 01:30.812
You're holding back.

01:30.815 --> 01:32.940
You really think I
want to feel this way?

01:32.942 --> 01:36.543
No matter how hard I try to get
it out, I don't feel any better.

01:39.240 --> 01:41.693
You're not the one I want to hurt.

01:49.658 --> 01:53.260
Give me a name.

01:53.262 --> 01:55.429
[LIGHTER CLICKS]

01:59.995 --> 02:02.229
I know my sister told
you guys to watch me,

02:02.232 --> 02:05.105
but this is getting kind
of creepy, don't you think?

02:07.142 --> 02:10.110
[SCOFFS]

02:10.112 --> 02:13.113
So, what? Hmm?

02:17.987 --> 02:19.886
[SCOFFS]

02:19.888 --> 02:22.388
What, am I supposed to
spend all eternity holed up

02:22.391 --> 02:24.091
in this stupid room?

02:27.863 --> 02:30.097
Will you guys just say something?

02:30.099 --> 02:33.300
[THUDDING, CRACKING]

02:35.000 --> 02:41.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:45.522 --> 02:47.322
Get it over with.

02:47.325 --> 02:50.659
Oh, I'm reserving that honor
for someone I love very much.

02:54.268 --> 02:59.447
- <font color="#D81D1D">Synced and corrected by VitoSilans</font> -
-- <font color="#138CE9">www.Addic7ed.com</font> --

02:59.450 --> 03:01.617
[WATER DRIPPING]

03:14.376 --> 03:16.510
[WOMAN GROANS]

03:24.987 --> 03:26.353
[WOMAN MOANING]

03:38.901 --> 03:40.667
[GASPS]

03:50.045 --> 03:51.578
[EXHALES]

03:51.580 --> 03:53.313
Vincent?

03:53.315 --> 03:55.841
I'm here.

03:55.844 --> 03:58.051
What ha... what happened?

03:58.053 --> 03:59.619
Emmett poisoned you.

04:03.992 --> 04:06.084
I thought I was dead.

04:07.763 --> 04:12.566
Ivy... you are.

04:16.404 --> 04:19.606
MARCEL: Josh, I'm at
the abandoned MSP plant.

04:19.608 --> 04:21.942
Emmett's up to something, and
I'm not just gonna sit around

04:21.944 --> 04:23.944
and let him get the drop on us.

04:23.946 --> 04:28.582
I may need backup, so when
you get this, call me back.

04:30.853 --> 04:33.053
I think I'm going mad.

04:33.055 --> 04:35.662
I-I keep blacking out,

04:35.665 --> 04:38.457
having these vague memories

04:38.460 --> 04:40.736
of conversations I can't fully recall.

04:40.739 --> 04:42.839
In the middle of the day, mind you.

04:42.842 --> 04:44.315
I'm sure it's nothing.

04:44.318 --> 04:45.432
No.

04:45.434 --> 04:47.334
Craziness runs in the family.

04:47.336 --> 04:49.794
My cousin Sean, my uncle Kieran.

04:49.797 --> 04:51.238
Right.

04:51.240 --> 04:52.439
Yeah.

04:52.441 --> 04:54.374
You knew them?

04:54.376 --> 04:57.502
Uh, you know, yeah, uh...

04:57.505 --> 04:59.841
Before I owned this place, I
worked with your cousin Cami,

04:59.844 --> 05:02.014
so I'm pretty sure she
mentioned their names.

05:02.017 --> 05:03.383
Right.

05:03.385 --> 05:04.851
Apparently, Sean and Kieran

05:04.853 --> 05:07.254
were happy as clams when they...

05:07.256 --> 05:08.909
when they killed themselves,

05:08.912 --> 05:10.859
right in the middle of the church.

05:10.862 --> 05:12.956
They were clergy,

05:12.959 --> 05:15.729
so I finally called up the archdiocese.

05:15.731 --> 05:18.999
Figured if I could get
ahold of their journals,

05:19.001 --> 05:20.410
I might be able to
find out what happened.

05:20.412 --> 05:21.568
Oh, Declan.

05:21.570 --> 05:22.803
I wouldn't do that.

05:22.805 --> 05:24.904
It's just...

05:24.907 --> 05:26.973
with all the stress you've been
under, and now you want to go

05:26.975 --> 05:29.276
digging up dirt on family suicides?

05:29.278 --> 05:32.112
Come on, man, you
should be taking it easy,

05:32.115 --> 05:33.847
you know? Do...

05:33.849 --> 05:35.949
do something fun.

05:40.155 --> 05:42.389
Speaking of fun.

05:44.480 --> 05:45.870
MAX: What do you say to...

05:45.873 --> 05:47.315
me buying you a drink,

05:47.318 --> 05:49.796
and you pretending to
find me interesting?

05:49.798 --> 05:52.632
Doesn't seem too difficult.

05:56.538 --> 05:58.205
[SPITS, COUGHING]

05:58.207 --> 05:59.973
[BUCKET CLATTERS]

05:59.975 --> 06:02.876
[CHAINS RATTLE]

06:06.748 --> 06:09.683
Have you decided how
you're going to kill him?

06:10.486 --> 06:12.652
HOPE: Slowly.

06:12.654 --> 06:14.955
Hope?

06:14.957 --> 06:17.427
Hope! Hey.

06:25.279 --> 06:27.300
I want to do this alone.

06:27.302 --> 06:28.635
What?

06:28.637 --> 06:31.338
This is supposed to help
me feel better, right?

06:31.340 --> 06:34.241
What's wrong with her?

06:34.243 --> 06:37.377
She has an affliction,

06:37.379 --> 06:42.582
for which your pain
is a momentary comfort.

06:44.353 --> 06:46.319
- My pain?
- HOPE: Mm-hmm.

06:46.321 --> 06:48.054
But I don't want an audience.

06:48.056 --> 06:49.154
Hope.

06:49.157 --> 06:50.656
If you want to help me, go.

06:53.054 --> 06:55.421
Well, I was rather hoping
to be part of the show.

06:57.084 --> 06:59.104
Well, consider starting small, then.

06:59.107 --> 07:01.174
Fingernails, or-or...

07:01.177 --> 07:03.737
perhaps the tongue.

07:03.739 --> 07:05.490
Build the suspense.

07:07.441 --> 07:09.291
Hey... hey, wait.

07:09.294 --> 07:12.045
You're not actually gonna
leave me with her, are you?

07:12.047 --> 07:14.214
Hey!

07:22.524 --> 07:24.558
VINCENT: <i>It's too late for Hope.</i>

07:24.560 --> 07:25.880
It's too late.

07:25.883 --> 07:28.027
Eventually, the darkness
is gonna overtake her,

07:28.030 --> 07:29.597
and the kid you know
is gonna be no more.

07:29.599 --> 07:30.800
I don't accept that.

07:30.803 --> 07:33.237
You know, she barely survived
this when she was eight.

07:33.240 --> 07:34.901
Now she's a budding adult,

07:34.903 --> 07:36.169
and she's one human kill away

07:36.171 --> 07:37.381
from triggering her werewolf side.

07:37.383 --> 07:38.882
Now, you think she's angry right now,

07:38.885 --> 07:41.479
you wait until those claws come
out and the eyes turn yellow.

07:41.482 --> 07:43.459
I need you to fix this.

07:43.462 --> 07:45.299
I don't know how to fix this, Elijah!

07:45.302 --> 07:46.346
Look around!

07:46.348 --> 07:48.245
All of these witches
just woke up from the dead

07:48.248 --> 07:50.012
with vampire blood coursing
through their veins.

07:50.014 --> 07:52.256
Now, as soon as their grief
gives them one second's pause,

07:52.258 --> 07:53.954
they're gonna have to decide
whether or not they're gonna

07:53.956 --> 07:57.440
feed and live forever, or end it all.

07:57.443 --> 07:59.510
They're my one and
only priority, Elijah.

07:59.513 --> 08:01.012
That's it.

08:04.433 --> 08:06.967
[PHONE VIBRATES]

08:11.473 --> 08:13.807
[DOOR CLATTERS, CREAKS]

08:41.039 --> 08:43.506
[SHOUTS]

08:45.772 --> 08:47.807
[MARCEL GRUNTING]

08:51.013 --> 08:52.612
The great Marcel Gerard.

08:52.615 --> 08:54.941
We've been waiting for you.

08:55.817 --> 08:57.384
[GROANING]

09:16.601 --> 09:18.835
ANTOINETTE: I wasn't
sure that you'd come.

09:18.838 --> 09:20.536
The conflict between our
families doesn't change

09:20.538 --> 09:22.007
the way I feel about you.

09:23.313 --> 09:25.765
But it complicates things.

09:29.749 --> 09:32.038
Roman was taken.

09:35.344 --> 09:37.110
Niklaus.

09:37.113 --> 09:40.348
Elijah, he's going to kill
him, if he hasn't already.

09:40.351 --> 09:42.382
He doesn't deserve to die.

09:42.385 --> 09:43.646
You and I both know

09:43.649 --> 09:45.481
that Roman got lost in the shadow

09:45.484 --> 09:47.535
of my mother, but she's dead now.

09:47.537 --> 09:50.004
And her hate shouldn't
be pinned on my brother.

09:50.006 --> 09:52.258
No, it shouldn't...

09:58.932 --> 10:02.270
If anything that you felt for me

10:02.273 --> 10:05.619
was real, talk to Klaus.

10:07.223 --> 10:09.423
Please.

10:18.380 --> 10:20.968
[GRUNTS]

10:24.474 --> 10:26.788
Don't bother. They're enchanted.

10:28.911 --> 10:30.820
You do see the irony here?

10:30.823 --> 10:33.067
Years ago, had someone threatened you,

10:33.070 --> 10:35.149
there would've been a legion of vampires

10:35.151 --> 10:37.351
searching to find and save you,

10:37.353 --> 10:41.622
but you forsook us, threw in
your lot with the Mikaelsons.

10:41.624 --> 10:45.459
Now no one is coming
because no one cares.

10:45.461 --> 10:47.257
You're on your own.

10:55.179 --> 10:57.840
So, I've tried dinner at Chophouse,

10:57.843 --> 10:59.968
music at Preservation Hall

10:59.971 --> 11:02.448
- but all I'm getting is a runaround?
- Well, I have to admit,

11:02.451 --> 11:05.285
you are very cute and
incredibly charming.

11:05.288 --> 11:07.081
But?

11:09.330 --> 11:12.385
Uh, it's just... in that uniform,

11:12.388 --> 11:13.988
you kind of remind me of someone.

11:13.990 --> 11:16.624
♪ Wanted to be loved... ♪

11:16.626 --> 11:18.624
He died a long time ago.

11:18.627 --> 11:22.429
♪ To be wanted, wanted... ♪

11:22.432 --> 11:24.965
Uh, his name was Aiden.

11:24.967 --> 11:27.368
I'm sorry.

11:27.370 --> 11:29.970
♪ Beware to know his love... ♪

11:29.972 --> 11:32.740
[SIGHS]

11:32.742 --> 11:34.842
To your lost love.

11:34.845 --> 11:39.648
To all we've loved and lost.

11:46.689 --> 11:50.658
Well... hope to see you around.

11:56.432 --> 12:00.167
♪ To be loved. ♪

12:04.941 --> 12:06.807
Would you believe it if I told you

12:06.809 --> 12:10.644
you were the reason
I came to New Orleans?

12:10.646 --> 12:13.380
I'd been hearing the stories for years,

12:13.382 --> 12:15.583
how the wolves and witches

12:15.585 --> 12:18.919
lived under the thumb of a true king.

12:20.790 --> 12:25.493
How the vampires lived
by a code of honor,

12:25.496 --> 12:28.866
loyalty to your own kind or else.

12:32.435 --> 12:36.337
What a disappointment
you turned out to be.

12:38.541 --> 12:40.976
Being a vampire wasn't enough.

12:40.979 --> 12:42.288
You thought you could be better,

12:42.291 --> 12:46.913
so you turned yourself
into an abomination.

12:46.916 --> 12:50.384
Well, at least your venom can
help us where you've failed.

13:02.689 --> 13:05.323
Did you know there are
stories about it, too?

13:05.326 --> 13:07.059
How it can take down

13:07.062 --> 13:11.105
a hybrid, an Original, even
Hope Mikaelson, whatever she is.

13:13.476 --> 13:16.429
Guess we'll see what it
can really do soon enough.

13:23.593 --> 13:25.804
How much time do I have?

13:25.807 --> 13:27.540
Days?

13:29.244 --> 13:31.110
Hours?

13:34.981 --> 13:37.815
Un-Unless...

13:37.818 --> 13:42.354
We feed, become vampires.

13:42.357 --> 13:45.692
It's the only way.

13:51.032 --> 13:53.633
I am who I am, Vincent.

13:53.635 --> 13:56.199
I was born a witch and
I will die that way.

13:56.202 --> 13:58.433
I'll say my good-byes
and then I'll move on.

13:58.436 --> 14:01.407
Hey, hey. Hey.

14:01.409 --> 14:03.936
Don't be sad.

14:03.939 --> 14:08.105
I've had visions of the
afterlife in the Ancestral Well

14:08.108 --> 14:11.643
and it is more beautiful
than you could ever imagine.

14:14.022 --> 14:16.089
[SNIFFLES]

14:16.091 --> 14:17.757
Beautiful?

14:17.760 --> 14:22.561
In my old house, where we
lived when I was little,

14:22.564 --> 14:26.933
the air is so thick with
honeysuckle and azaleas

14:26.935 --> 14:29.168
you could almost wrap yourself up in it.

14:31.072 --> 14:33.616
Oh, Ivy.

14:36.444 --> 14:38.710
Babe, uh...

14:38.713 --> 14:40.145
[SNIFFLES]

14:40.148 --> 14:42.082
...there's something I got to show you.

14:43.819 --> 14:45.401
ROMAN: I know you won't believe this,

14:45.404 --> 14:47.352
but I've been trying to see you, okay?

14:47.355 --> 14:49.686
You're right. I don't believe it.

14:52.727 --> 14:55.436
[GRUNTS, PANTS] I-I swear.

14:55.439 --> 14:57.104
My sister, she wanted
me to leave the country,

14:57.106 --> 14:58.814
but I wouldn't go until
I got to talk to you.

14:58.816 --> 15:00.449
Is this the kind of
talk you had in mind?

15:00.452 --> 15:01.765
Look, I-I know.

15:01.768 --> 15:04.436
Taking part in your mother's
capture and tricking you,

15:04.439 --> 15:05.505
that was wrong and I know that.

15:05.507 --> 15:07.507
And yet you did it anyway!

15:07.509 --> 15:08.875
[GRUNTING]

15:10.812 --> 15:13.746
[COUGHS]

15:13.748 --> 15:16.449
No, you... you have to understand.

15:16.451 --> 15:18.468
For years I've been told to fear you,

15:18.471 --> 15:20.086
every day, every night,

15:20.088 --> 15:21.687
stories of what your father did to mine,

15:21.689 --> 15:23.556
- what you and your kind have done to us.
- My kind?

15:23.558 --> 15:26.058
No, no, no, I like you, Hope,
okay? I like you, I really do.

15:26.060 --> 15:28.127
I just didn't know whether to
listen to the voice in my head

15:28.129 --> 15:29.862
that said you were good
or my mother's voice

15:29.864 --> 15:32.398
that said over and over
y-you and your family...

15:32.400 --> 15:35.468
My family's what?

15:35.470 --> 15:37.503
Evil.

15:37.505 --> 15:41.073
[INDISTINCT WHISPERING]

15:41.075 --> 15:43.316
And I wasn't strong enough to fight her.

15:43.319 --> 15:45.718
And I don't want you to forgive me.

15:45.721 --> 15:46.696
I just want you to know

15:46.699 --> 15:50.348
that I know what I did was wrong. Okay?

15:50.351 --> 15:52.985
[INDISTINCT WHISPERING]

15:52.987 --> 15:56.589
So, if you need to, just...

15:56.591 --> 15:58.457
kill me.

15:58.459 --> 16:00.927
[WHISPERING CONTINUES]

16:06.467 --> 16:09.335
So this is the new parenting style?

16:09.337 --> 16:12.672
Allowing your daughter to
mercilessly torture that boy.

16:12.674 --> 16:15.476
That boy held her and Hayley hostage,

16:15.479 --> 16:18.347
almost killed Hope and
succeeded with her mother.

16:18.350 --> 16:20.642
So, if my daughter
decides to end his life,

16:20.645 --> 16:23.315
then that would make her someone
who vanquishes her enemies,

16:23.318 --> 16:26.007
following in the
footsteps of her father...

16:26.010 --> 16:27.376
and her uncle.

16:27.379 --> 16:29.622
She was supposed to be
better than us, Niklaus.

16:29.624 --> 16:31.657
She's ill.

16:31.659 --> 16:34.894
If this brings her some relief,
then nothing else matters.

16:34.896 --> 16:36.226
And then what?

16:36.229 --> 16:38.374
When she's done with him
and the darkness returns?

16:38.377 --> 16:40.452
I'm sorry, but I have to ask,

16:40.455 --> 16:43.601
as much as I enjoy
your withering judgment,

16:43.604 --> 16:45.737
do you really have Hope's
best interest at heart?

16:45.740 --> 16:48.780
- What are you accusing me of?
- I'm not blind, Elijah.

16:48.783 --> 16:51.032
If you love that woman
so much, go be with her.

16:51.035 --> 16:52.801
I have my own family to worry about

16:52.804 --> 16:54.272
and that boy is collateral damage.

16:54.275 --> 16:55.973
You are leading your
daughter down a path

16:55.976 --> 16:57.405
that will erase her humanity.

16:57.408 --> 16:59.185
And if she loses that, Niklaus,

16:59.187 --> 17:00.253
the consequences will be

17:00.255 --> 17:01.354
devastating for everyone.

17:01.356 --> 17:03.749
- Just don't.
- Don't what?

17:03.752 --> 17:06.199
Counsel you against
your worst instincts?

17:06.202 --> 17:08.535
A thousand years, I have
desperately tried to sway you

17:08.538 --> 17:11.297
toward some kind of reason.

17:11.299 --> 17:12.832
And for a thousand years,

17:12.834 --> 17:14.567
I've trusted you.

17:14.569 --> 17:17.403
So now what?

17:17.405 --> 17:21.507
Our lives may be forever,

17:21.516 --> 17:23.569
but our allegiance is not.

17:26.981 --> 17:29.015
[SCOFFS]

17:32.120 --> 17:34.553
Okay. So...

17:34.555 --> 17:37.623
Ivy, right now is one
of those rare instances

17:37.625 --> 17:39.959
where you are neither of
the world of the living

17:39.961 --> 17:42.428
or the world of the dead, so
you can pass between the two

17:42.430 --> 17:43.562
and I can come with you.

17:43.564 --> 17:45.798
All right, give me your hand, babe.

17:50.571 --> 17:53.306
- [GASPS]
- I know, I know. I know.

18:02.083 --> 18:05.151
<i>Prezéve lyen lavi nou.</i>

18:05.265 --> 18:09.555
<i>Prezéve lyen lavi nou.</i>

18:09.557 --> 18:12.992
[SHUDDERING]: <i>Prezéve lyen lavi nou.</i>

18:26.641 --> 18:29.241
[WOMAN CRYING]

18:33.348 --> 18:35.548
[MAN GROANING LOUDLY]

18:40.321 --> 18:42.922
[WOMAN CRYING]

18:44.859 --> 18:47.193
[WOMAN SOBBING]

18:50.040 --> 18:52.207
No!

18:52.210 --> 18:53.666
I-Is this...

18:53.668 --> 18:56.412
The Ancestral Well, Ivy.
New Orleans witches have been

18:56.415 --> 18:57.849
coming here at the time of their deaths

18:57.851 --> 18:59.504
since there's been a New Orleans, okay?

18:59.507 --> 19:01.507
All of their power gets
trapped right in here.

19:01.509 --> 19:03.776
We use it, but while we grow stronger,

19:03.778 --> 19:05.378
the dead just languish.

19:07.415 --> 19:09.715
This is where you're
gonna end up when you die.

19:09.717 --> 19:11.150
[MAN GROANING LOUDLY]

19:11.152 --> 19:12.485
This is a lie.

19:12.487 --> 19:13.527
Ivy...

19:13.530 --> 19:15.421
I know what I saw, Vincent.

19:15.424 --> 19:17.756
I know where I'm
supposed to get my peace.

19:17.759 --> 19:19.058
Now get me out of here.

19:19.060 --> 19:21.961
- Ivy...
- Get me out of here right now!

19:23.452 --> 19:26.171
He simply won't respond to reason.

19:26.174 --> 19:28.968
So, then... what now?

19:28.970 --> 19:32.104
Those who once followed your mother,

19:32.106 --> 19:34.473
do you think they'll
respond to your leadership?

19:34.475 --> 19:38.007
You're asking me to take up her mantle

19:38.010 --> 19:39.879
in a war against your brother?

19:39.881 --> 19:41.929
I'm asking you to gather them.

19:44.172 --> 19:46.139
I'm asking you to have faith in me.

19:48.890 --> 19:51.457
You have no idea what you took from me.

19:51.459 --> 19:53.726
My mother. My children's grandmother,

19:53.728 --> 19:55.577
someone to hold me when I'm scared

19:55.580 --> 19:57.345
and to call me when I'm lonely,

19:57.348 --> 19:59.013
the-the first eyes I ever looked into,

19:59.016 --> 20:01.566
- I mean, my best friend!
- I do. Okay, I really do.

20:01.569 --> 20:04.504
- No, you don't! You can't.
- Hope, I lost my mother, too.

20:04.507 --> 20:07.106
- What did you just say?
- [INDISTINCT WHISPERING]

20:07.108 --> 20:10.249
Your mother...

20:10.252 --> 20:12.244
was nothing like mine.

20:12.246 --> 20:14.747
[GRUNTS]

20:14.749 --> 20:17.149
[PANTS] That's-that's not what I meant.

20:17.151 --> 20:19.280
That's exactly what you meant!

20:21.622 --> 20:24.690
[INDISTINCT WHISPERING]

20:27.495 --> 20:30.288
[PANTING]

20:30.291 --> 20:31.957
[HOPE SCREAMS]

20:35.136 --> 20:37.903
[SHOUTS]

20:37.905 --> 20:39.939
[PANTING]

20:39.941 --> 20:41.607
Hope, Hope.

20:41.609 --> 20:43.776
What?!

20:43.778 --> 20:46.612
Your arm.

20:46.614 --> 20:47.646
[PANTING]

20:47.648 --> 20:49.849
[WHIMPERS]

20:50.985 --> 20:52.885
[WHISPERING CONTINUES]

20:58.806 --> 21:00.702
HOPE: What's happening to me?

21:00.705 --> 21:01.968
KLAUS: I don't know.

21:01.969 --> 21:03.815
It's bad, right?

21:03.818 --> 21:05.752
[INDISTINCT WHISPERING]

21:05.754 --> 21:08.178
You need to rid yourself
of this darkness.

21:08.181 --> 21:09.888
I can't. I can't kill him.

21:09.891 --> 21:10.890
I won't.

21:10.892 --> 21:11.921
- Hope.
- Dad.

21:11.924 --> 21:12.956
He's no more guilty

21:12.959 --> 21:15.393
or responsible than me.

21:19.734 --> 21:21.546
All that power,

21:21.549 --> 21:23.702
still merciful.

21:23.705 --> 21:26.655
You clearly didn't get that
from my side of the family.

21:29.411 --> 21:31.577
[INDISTINCT WHISPERING]

21:35.884 --> 21:39.485
This is only gonna get worse, isn't it?

21:46.030 --> 21:47.463
Stay here.

21:49.811 --> 21:51.362
KLAUS: <i>You shouldn't be here, brother.</i>

21:51.365 --> 21:52.732
Niklaus, I think I have a solution.

21:52.734 --> 21:54.122
You really think you can act as counsel

21:54.124 --> 21:55.234
when you're sleeping with the enemy?

21:55.236 --> 21:57.337
I'm not speaking for Antoinette,
nor am I speaking for Roman.

21:57.339 --> 21:58.334
This is about Hope.

21:58.337 --> 21:59.603
Oh, so this is about Hope, now.

21:59.606 --> 22:01.140
How touching you remembered her plight.

22:01.142 --> 22:02.975
She's faltering, isn't she, Niklaus?

22:02.977 --> 22:04.610
That rage,

22:04.612 --> 22:05.945
consuming her from within.

22:05.947 --> 22:08.421
And yet, you've taken
me from her side again.

22:08.424 --> 22:11.178
You might not trust me right
at this moment, Niklaus...

22:12.620 --> 22:15.217
...do you really have any other choice?

22:19.959 --> 22:22.228
IVY: <i>Before this happened,</i>

22:22.230 --> 22:25.431
everything was clear to me.

22:25.433 --> 22:29.147
I could close my eyes and see my peace.

22:32.629 --> 22:35.229
My father is there.

22:35.232 --> 22:39.735
He died when I was a baby,
but he is there, waiting.

22:39.738 --> 22:41.738
And when he sees me,

22:41.741 --> 22:44.972
he takes me in his arms, and he says,

22:44.975 --> 22:48.354
"My sweet girl,

22:48.356 --> 22:51.190
I missed you so."

22:54.896 --> 22:56.961
[WHIMPERS]

22:56.964 --> 23:00.365
But you're saying

23:00.368 --> 23:02.869
everything I see is a lie?

23:02.871 --> 23:05.366
I am telling you that you have a choice.

23:05.369 --> 23:06.631
I made my choice.

23:07.384 --> 23:08.783
You don't belong in the Well.

23:08.786 --> 23:10.753
And I can't become a vampire.

23:14.479 --> 23:16.850
So, then, what will become of me?

23:21.055 --> 23:23.256
[BOAT HORN BLOWS]

23:37.514 --> 23:38.880
[ENGINE STARTS]

23:49.184 --> 23:50.631
[EXHALES]

24:14.075 --> 24:15.441
[CHAIN RATTLES]

24:20.315 --> 24:21.614
No.

24:21.616 --> 24:23.282
Josh. Don't. No.

24:52.017 --> 24:53.717
♪ ♪

25:20.842 --> 25:21.908
[GRUNTS]

25:26.447 --> 25:27.647
[EXHALES]

25:27.649 --> 25:29.115
What is it?

25:29.117 --> 25:30.316
Huh?

25:30.318 --> 25:32.518
[PANTING]

25:35.857 --> 25:37.456
Josh, what's wrong?

25:37.458 --> 25:38.936
Uh...

25:48.736 --> 25:51.737
That can't be good, right?

25:58.647 --> 26:01.156
Hey. Come here. Sit down.

26:01.159 --> 26:02.358
Sit.

26:02.361 --> 26:04.495
Lay back.

26:04.498 --> 26:06.531
Marcel.

26:06.534 --> 26:07.422
I'll call Freya.

26:07.425 --> 26:08.851
- Marcel.
- No, I'm gonna get the cure.

26:08.853 --> 26:09.718
Marcel.

26:09.721 --> 26:11.450
Try to hold still so the poison

26:11.453 --> 26:12.515
won't move through your system.

26:12.517 --> 26:14.646
It's already in my heart.

26:14.649 --> 26:17.216
You've got to believe me, okay?

26:17.220 --> 26:19.986
[PANTING]

26:27.128 --> 26:28.561
I leave town for a few years,

26:28.563 --> 26:30.196
and suddenly, you know everything?

26:30.198 --> 26:31.731
[CHUCKLES]

26:31.733 --> 26:33.799
I always knew everything.

26:33.801 --> 26:36.694
I just played dumb so
you'd put up with me.

26:41.643 --> 26:43.776
Hey, you, uh...

26:44.812 --> 26:47.513
...you remember the first day we met?

26:48.750 --> 26:51.550
Yeah, you wouldn't pick up that coin.

26:52.787 --> 26:54.020
Even if it meant you died,

26:54.023 --> 26:56.121
you still wouldn't betray your friend.

26:56.124 --> 27:00.626
Luckily for me, you've got
your whole loyalty thing.

27:02.580 --> 27:04.346
And, uh,

27:04.349 --> 27:07.800
I know that that's the only
reason you spared me that day.

27:07.802 --> 27:09.468
Mm-mmm.

27:09.470 --> 27:12.705
But now,

27:12.707 --> 27:15.908
you are my family.

27:18.112 --> 27:20.212
Same.

27:24.367 --> 27:26.567
[CHOKING, GAGGING]

27:27.778 --> 27:29.178
Hey.

27:41.202 --> 27:42.868
[KISSES]

27:51.346 --> 27:53.546
[SNIFFLING]

28:03.057 --> 28:04.575
[BILL GRUNTS]

28:04.578 --> 28:07.065
The archdiocese has been meaning
to have these files shipped

28:07.068 --> 28:09.747
to the library at St.
Patrick's for years.

28:09.750 --> 28:10.997
This Kieran O'Connell.

28:11.000 --> 28:12.279
He's your uncle, right?

28:12.282 --> 28:14.763
Yes. Thank you. Thanks a million.

28:14.766 --> 28:16.132
That means a lot.

28:16.135 --> 28:18.703
Let me see if there's some more here.

28:18.706 --> 28:20.339
This might be one.

28:20.341 --> 28:21.941
Let's check this out.

28:23.478 --> 28:25.878
I asked you here

28:25.880 --> 28:29.536
because you've all been
loyal to my mother's cause.

28:31.732 --> 28:33.686
